Heat the Melt in a deep wok or a saucepan over medium heat. Add the onion, ginger and pepper and saute for 15 minutes, until all veggies are wilted and browning. Add the garlic and saute for 1 minute. Add the chickpeas and spices and cook for 3 minutes. Then add the tomatoes and cook another 2 minutes. Add the coconut milk and combine. Bring the mixture to a boil and cook 10 minutes to thicken slightly. Serve over rice.